
Comparable Interface :-
------------------------------
1. It provides single sorting sequence. 
2. Based on single element we can do sorting such as id, name, etc
3. Comparable affects the original class, i.e., the actual class is modified.
4. we can use compareTo() method to sort the elements.
5. It is present in java.lang package
6. We can sort the list elements of Comparable type by Collections.sort(List) method.

Comparator Interface :-
-----------------------------
1. It provides multiple sorting sequence.
2. Comparator doesn't affect the original class, i.e., the actual class is not modified.
3. we can use compare() method to sort the elements.
4. It is present in java.util.package.
5. We can sort the list elements of Comparator type by Collections.sort(List, Comparator) method.